      "instruction": "<p>Divide the <strong>pizza sauce</strong> between your <strong>tortillas </strong>(make sure to only cover one half of the tortilla with the sauce!)</p><p>Top the sauce evenly with the <strong>grated cheddar</strong>, <strong>chopped basil</strong>, <strong>pepperoni slices </strong>and <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Fold each tortilla over so you're left with 6 <span class=\"text-purple\">[9]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[12] </span>half moon-shaped sandwiches – these are your <strong>loaded quesadillas</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600415889711-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600415889711-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600415889711-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600415889711-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1600415889711-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>loaded quesadillas </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Place a second baking tray on top to weigh them down slightly</p><p>Put the stacked baking trays in the oven and cook for 12 min, or until the quesadillas are slightly browned and the cheese has melted</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600415898959-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600415898959-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600415898959-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600415898959-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1600415898959-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper<strong> </strong>and shred</p><p>Chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> finely</p><p>Combine your<strong> mayo </strong>with your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>creamy dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1600415910705-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1600415910705-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1600415910705-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1600415910705-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1600415910705-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the quesadillas are slightly browned, remove the stacked trays from the oven and leave them to cool for 1 min</p><p>Tip: This makes it easier to transfer the quesadillas to a board without losing any filling!</p><p>Chop the <strong>quesadillas</strong> in half – these are your <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>pepperoni pizza quesadillas</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1600415925308-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1600415925308-x400.jpg",
